BC Lorem Ipsum TODO
=================================================

There are still quite a lot of features we could
add to BC Lorem Ipsum extension.

A few users of BC Lorem Ipsum may require further
extension of the solution and related features.

If you are interested in sponsoring the development
of any of these features for your eZ Publish web site,
please contact info@brookinsconsulting.com


Features for consideration:

- Add new command line script to create nodes using a matrix of parameters instead. Allows for greater creation parameter flexibility
-- IE: ./extension/bcloremipsum/bin/php/bcloremipsum.php --create --params=(multiple separated by comma ',' char; int node_id),-(multiple separated by dash '-' char; int class_id).(multiple separated by period '.' char; int count)
-- Example usage: ./extension/bcloremipsum/bin/php/bcloremipsum.php --create --params=2-16.10,190-16-1.20.10,42-16-1-19.40.20.80
-- Refactor BCLoremIpsum class method createNodes to support this creation style of parameters
- Add support for command line script and module view to default to node_id 2
- Add support for command line script and module view to default to array of classes to use to generate content based on (default selected is only one class)
- Add support for the create module view to use Quick Mode as default selected option
- Add support for additional datatypes
-- Add support for the ezauthor datatype
-- Add support for the ezemail datatype
-- Add support for the ezbinaryfile datatype
-- Add support for the ezidentifier datatype
-- Add support for the ezobjectrelationlist datatype
-- Add support for the ezurl datatype
-- Add support for the ezmedia datatype
-- Add support for the ezmatrix datatype
-- Add support for the ezisbn datatype
-- Add support for the ezselection datatype
-- Add support for the ezsrrating datatype
-- Add support for the ezgmaplocation datatype
-- Add support for the ezobjectrelation datatype
- Add support to BCLoremIpsum class method createNodes method to create by class-ids (array) not one single class-id
- Add documentation support additions required by custom datatypes
- Update design templates to include create progress within standard pagelayout template (ini setting based option, default to standard pagelayout)
- Any other changes not mentioned here

